id, until lamb is tender. Garnish with mint and serve with fresh chillies and side of choice."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Lamb and spice paste","content":["500 g boneless lamb shoulder, cut into pieces (approx. 4 cm)","3 tsp garlic paste (see Tips)","1 tbsp ginger paste, plus 1 tsp extra (see Tips)","2 tsp salt","100 g toor dal (see Tips)","50 g mung dal (see Tips)","50 g chana dal (see Tips)","hot water, for soaking","2 tsp cumin seeds","2 tsp coriander seeds","1 cinnamon quill","1 tbsp black peppercorns","4 cardamom pods (green)","2 cardamom pods (black)","2 dried bay leaves","1 tsp fenugreek seeds","4 fresh long green chillies, trimmed and cut into halves, plus extra sliced to serve"]},{"title":"Masala","content":["1 tbsp ghee (see Tips)","2 - 3 brown onions (approx. 360 g), cut into quarters","½ tsp ground turmeric","300 g fresh tomatoes (approx. 3 tomatoes), cut into quarters","1 tbsp tamarind paste (see Tips)","1 tsp salt","200 g water","100 g pumpkin flesh, cut into pieces (2 cm)","fresh mint leaves, for garnishing"]}],"id":"r132112","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-L_6ezTIh-xU\/XZQxVP6uzNI\/AAAAAAAAcuA\/cyg1SU7XfYkNearKHXW5kC6N0bTteNZ8QCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_pXZAUkEXS0_bxC5d.png","title":"Lamb dhansak","publishedAt":"2017-07-03T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"23.9 g","fat":"25.4 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"20.3 g","calories":"1763 kJ \/ 419 kcal"},"usefulItems":"bowl, plastic wrap, large bowl, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["To make your own garlic paste, ginger paste, ghee and Tamarind paste, please refer to the recipes on this recipe chip.","Toor dal (split yellow lentils), mung dal (dried split mung beans) and chana dal (dried brown chick peas) can all be found at Indian food stores or online.","You can serve this with rice, bread, chutney or your favourite side. We served ours with Garlic and coriander naan (please refer to the recipe on this recipe chip).<br><br>"],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","25h 45m","6 portions"]}